    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix segfault in RRC state checking function\n\n### Summary\nThe newly added `check_rrc_state()` function in the RC RAN function module can cause a segmentation fault when called with certain RNTI values. The issue occurs due to improper bounds checking in the simulation logic.\n\nThis fix corrects the conditional logic to ensure all RNTI values are handled properly.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E2AP/RAN_FUNCTION/O-RAN/ran_func_rc.c`: Fixed boundary conditions in RRC state simulation.\n- `openair2/E2AP/RAN_FUNCTION/O-RAN/ran_func_rc.h`: Updated function documentation.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Call `check_rrc_state(200)` \n2. Observe that the function incorrectly returns RRC_CONNECTED\n3. Call `check_rrc_state(65535)` \n4. Segmentation fault occurs due to integer overflow in comparison\n\nThe fix ensures proper handling of all valid RNTI values (1-65535) and maintains the expected state mapping behavior.\n"
}